HEADWORD: Debacchate
<hw>De*bac"chate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>debacchatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>debacchari</ets> to rage;
<ets>de-</ets> + <ets>bacchari</ets> to rage like a bacchant.]</ety>
<def>To rave as a bacchanal.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Cockeram.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

